from langchain_genai import ChatGoogleGenerativeAI
from dotenv import load_dotenv
import os
load_dotenv()
llm = ChatGoogleGenerativeAI(
    model="gemini-2.5-flash",
    google_api_key=os.getenv("GEMINI_API_KEY"),
    temperature=0.2,
    max_tokens=100,
    top_p=0.4,
    top_k=50,
    min_tokens=10,
    context_window=2048,
    stop_sequences=["\n\n"],
    frequency_penalty=0.5,
    presence_penalty=0.5,
    seed=42
)

prompt = input("Enter your Prompt here: ")

for chunk in llm.stream(prompt):
        print(chunk.content, end="", flush=True)




"""
1-TEMPERATURE: Controls the randomness of the output. Higher values (e.g., 0.8) make the output more 
random, while lower values (e.g., 0.2) make it more focused and deterministic.
Temperature controls: how predictable or how creative the model behaves during token generation.
temperature use cases:
| Use Case          | Recommended Temperature |
| ----------------- | ----------------------- |
| Coding agents     | 0.0-0.2                 |
| RAG systems       | 0.1-0.3                 |
| Customer support  | 0.2-0.5                 |
| Research agents   | 0.2-0.4                 |
| Autonomous agents | 0.3-0.7                 |
| Brainstorming     | 0.7-1.0                 |
| Creative writing  | 0.8-1.2                 |
Many beginners think:

“Higher temperature = smarter AI”
That is incorrect.
Temperature affects randomness,variation, creativity, NOT intelligence.
The model knowledge remains the same.
"""

"""
2-MAX_TOKENS: Sets the maximum number of tokens (words or subwords) that the model can generate in its response. 
This limits the length of the output. 
LLMs has two separate token limits: input tokens and output tokens. max_tokens refers to the output token limit, which controls how long the generated response can be.
This is useful for ensuring that the response does not exceed a certain length,
which can be important for applications with character limits or when you want to control the verbosity of the output.
| Item          | Tokens |
| ------------- | ------ |
| System Prompt | 500    |
| Chat History  | 1000   |
| User Query    | 200    |
| max_tokens    | 300    |
Total possible context:
500 + 1000 + 200 + 300 = 2000 tokens

Why It Matters in AI Agents
| Factor                | Impact                              |
| --------------------- | ----------------------------------- |
| Cost                  | More tokens = more money            |
