| Reasoning depth       | More space to think                 |
| JSON completion       | Too low may cut output              |
| Tool calling          | Truncated responses can break tools |
| Memory usage          | Large outputs consume context       |
| Multi-agent workflows | Token explosion risk                |

Recommended Values for Agents
| Use Case            | Recommended max_tokens |
| ------------------- | ---------------------- |
| Chatbot             | 200-500                |
| Coding assistant    | 1000-4000              |
| RAG agent           | 300-800                |
| JSON extraction     | 200-600                |
| Autonomous agent    | 1000-3000              |
| Research summarizer | 1500-5000              |
| Customer support    | 150-400                |

"""
"""3-TOP_P: Implements nucleus sampling, top_p controls how many probable token choices the model is allowed to consider before generating the next token.
| top_p | Behavior     |
| ----- | ------------ |
| 0.1   | Very strict  |
| 0.3   | Conservative |
| 0.5   | Balanced     |
| 0.9   | Diverse      |
| 1.0   | No filtering |

P(t1)+P(t2)+⋯+P(tn​)≥p

“Keep adding the most probable tokens until their total probability becomes greater than or equal to p.
Suppose the LLM predicts the next word probabilities like this:
| Token    | Probability |
| -------- | ----------- |
| "cat"    | 0.40        |
| "dog"    | 0.30        |
| "rabbit" | 0.15        |
| "tiger"  | 0.10        |
| "dragon" | 0.05        |
0.40 + 0.30 + 0.15 + 0.10 + 0.05 = 1.00

if top_p = 0.70
The model starts from the highest probability token.
step 1 Add: cat = 0.40
Current total: 0.40
Still less than 0.70.

step 2 Add: dog = 0.30
Current total:  0.40 + 0.30 = 0.70
Condition satisfied:
0.40+0.30≥0.70
So the allowed token pool becomes: cat,dog
Everything else is discarded.

Top-P controls:
“How wide the model’s decision space is.”
Smaller top_p:narrow thinking, focused outputs
Larger top_p:broader exploration,creative outputs

Math Behind the Scenes:
1. The model generates a probability distribution over the next possible tokens.
Prompt
   ↓
Neural Network
   ↓
Logits
   ↓
Softmax
   ↓
Probabilities
   ↓
Top-P Filtering
   ↓
Token Sampling
