# TOP_K: Limits the number of tokens to consider at each step to the top K most likely tokens (e.g., 50). This can help in reducing the chances of generating less relevant or nonsensical tokens.

"""
# MIN_TOKENS: Sets the minimum number of tokens that the model must generate in its
# response. This ensures that the output is of a certain length, which can be useful for tasks that require more detailed answers.
# CONTEXT_WINDOW: Defines the maximum number of tokens that the model can consider as input context
# STOP_SEQUENCES: Specifies one or more sequences of tokens that, when generated, will cause the model to stop generating further output. This can be used to control the format of the response or to prevent the model from generating unwanted content.
# FREQUENCY_PENALTY: Adjusts the likelihood of the model repeating the same tokens. A higher value (e.g., 0.5) penalizes frequent tokens, encouraging more diverse output.
# PRESENCE_PENALTY: Similar to frequency penalty, but it penalizes tokens based on whether they have already appeared in the generated text. This encourages the model to introduce new topics or ideas rather than repeating the same ones.
# SEED: Sets a specific seed for random number generation, which can help in producing reproducible outputs. Using the same seed with the same prompt and settings will yield the same response from the model.  
